ion: An Explanation in Theory |first= Major Lisa |last= Nemeth|year=2009 |url= http://www.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?Location=U2&doc=GetTRDoc.pdf&AD=ADA506197|format=pdf |publisher= School of Advanced Military Studies, United States Army Command and General Staff College, Fort Leavenworth, Kansas }} <!-- Tanous 2003 {{Sfn| Tanous |2003}}--> *{{Cite journal|ref=harv |title= Building a Psychological Strategy for the U.S.: Leveraging the Informational Element of National Power |first= Lieutenant Colonel Stephen M. |last= Tanous |date=7 April 2003 |url= http://www.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?AD=ADA414554&Location=U2&doc=GetTRDoc.pdf |series=USAWC STRATEGY RESEARCH PROJECT |publisher= U.S. Army War College, Carlisle Barracks, Pennsylvania }} <!--Template for chapters by different authors--> <!--{{Sfn| | }} --> *{{Cite book|ref=harv|title= The Use of Force: Military Power and International Politics |chapter= |first= |last= |pages= |editor1-first=Robert J.|editor1-last=Art |editor2-first= Kenneth Neal |editor2-last= Waltz |isbn=978-074252557-3 |publisher= Rowman & Littlefield |year=2004 }} *Hill, Norman. "Was There an Ultimatum Before Pearl Harbour?". [[American Journal of International Law]]. Vol 42. No 2. Apr 1948. p 335. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/2193677 JSTOR]. *Lauren, Paul Gorden. "Ultimata and Coercive Diplomacy". [[International Studies Quarterly]]. Vol 16. No 2. Jun 1972. p 131. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/3013977 JSTOR].
